    Step aside, YAML

    Kanvas is here

    Friends don't let friends GitOps alone.

    Kanvas Modes

    Operator Mode

    Operator offers an interactive topology of your Kubernetes clusters with live terminal sessions, log streaming and performance testing of your applications. Designs created in Designer mode can be deployed and viewed as running in your environment using Operator.

    Explore
    Designer Mode

    Drag-and-drop your cloud native infrastructure using a palette of thousands of versioned Kubernetes components and Cloud services. Collaborate wtih teammates using this self-service engineering platform. Using GitOps? Integrate advanced performance analysis into your pipeline.

    Explore

    Designer

    Discover and model your cloud native deployments

    Drag-and-drop your cloud native infrastructure using a palette of thousands of versioned Kubernetes components. Using GitOps? Integrate advanced performance analysis into your pipeline.

    Operator

    Apply patterns and manage many Kubernetes clusters

    Deploy designs, apply patterns, manage and operate your deployments in real-time. Bring all your Kubernetes clusters under a common point of management. Interactively connect to terminal sessions or initiate and search log streams from your containers.

    ❝ I love visuals for creating IaC. I think it can be amazingly impactful for self-serve platforms for developers. ❞

    Guy Menahem

    Software Engineer at AWS

    Design

    Learn more

    • Design your deployments the way you want

      Drag-and-drop your cloud native infrastructure using a palette of thousands of versioned Kubernetes components and Cloud services. Say goodbye to YAML configurations.

    • Manage your applications visually and intuitively

      Play with powerful features including context-aware designs and namespace configurations to easily manage all services.

    • Build the bridge

      Go from developer handoffs to ongoing conversations with a shared language between design and development.

    • Stop finger-pointing

      Make infrastructure and application management less about finger-pointing and more about collaborating.

    ❝ The fact that Kanvas automatically renders our Kubernetes configuration is a game-changer for our team. ❞

    Kaur Kallas

    Software Architect at Entigo

    Operate

    Learn more

    • All your Kubernetes and Cloud infrastructure under a common management

      Deploy designs, apply patterns, manage and operate your deployments and services in real-time.

    • Continuous visibility across all of your clusters and workloads.

      Import your existing Kubernetes, Kustomize, Helm, or Docker Compose applications. Interactively connect to terminal sessions or initiate and search log streams from your containers.

    ❝ Wow, just tried Kanvas and it's exactly what I needed! Dragging that Helm chart was so smooth, and the smart features really caught my attention. Definitely sharing this with my dev team before everyone else discovers it! ❞

    Abdechakour Hrouchan

    Software Engineer at Atlas Cloud Services

    Collaborate

    Learn more

    • Bring those ideas to life

      Designer and Operator live side-by-side, so all design work, from ideation to operation, can be found in one place.

    • Create. Iterate. Repeat.

      Build an iterative design flow with live collaboration that keeps you in the loop whether you're working in the office or remotely.

    • Where your teams share the same language

      Build an iterative design flow with live collaboration that keeps you in the loop whether you're working in the office or remotely.

    • Inclusive collaboration from start to finish

      Kanvas is an end-to-end management platform, here to help teams understand problems, explore options, and build solutions—together.

    ❝ Kanvas is unreal. Support for air-gapped deployments is all the better, too. ❞

    Phillip Ulberg

    Solutions Architect at Raymond James Financial, Inc.

    Kanvas is a sophisticated and delightfully intuitive tool for designing and operating cloud native infrastructure for Kubernetes and Clouds. Choose freestyle composition of your infrastructure by drawing shapes, lines, text, and icons to represent the components and relationships of your Kubernetes clusters or quickstart by selecting a pattern the catalog of predefined templates.
